\description{
Internal helpers implementing DMSTA hydrologic integration, including
within-day control depth interpolation, derivative evaluation, and RK4 stepping.

Internal helper to interpolate a daily control depth time series within a day
using one of three DMSTA interpolation conventions:
\itemize{
\item \code{1}: inputs treated as daily means (no within-day variation)
\item \code{2}: inputs treated as mid-day values (DMSTA default)
\item \code{3}: inputs treated as end-of-day values
}

Internal helper corresponding to one derivative evaluation (DMSTA "DerivFlow")
used by the Runge-Kutta integrator. Given current volume and forcing inputs,
computes net fluxes, outflow, seepage, bypass, and the instantaneous rate of
change in volume (\code{dvdt}).

Internal helper that performs one Runge-Kutta 4th order (RK4) sub-step for
hydrologic volume using \code{dmsta_deriv_flow()} for derivative evaluations.

Internal helper that integrates hydrologic volume and fluxes over one day
using \code{Nsteps} RK4 sub-steps. Returns daily totals/diagnostics and
(optionally) per-substep details in \code{meta$steps}.

Similar to \code{dmsta_flow_day()} but returns the per-substep mean rates
explicitly in the \code{steps} element (useful for coupling to constituent
transport/biogeochemistry that needs sub-daily hydrology).
}
\details{
Missing values are handled defensively:
\itemize{
\item if today's \code{Zcontrol} is \code{NA}, it is treated as \code{0}
\item if neighbor days are \code{NA}, they fall back to today's value
}
The interpolation fraction \code{delta} is clamped to \eqn{[0,1]}.

Control depth is interpolated within the day via \code{dmsta_interp_zcontrol()}
using the RK stage timing defined by \code{step_index}, \code{nsteps}, and
\code{step_frac}.

Returns the updated volume (with safety clamp to minimum volume) along with
stage-averaged fluxes for outflow, seepage, bypass, and ET.
}
